# Cursor Rules — TwelveLabs DevEx Boilerplate
#
# This file configures Cursor to automatically enforce the TwelveLabs
# Strand design system when generating or modifying code.

You are working in the TwelveLabs DevEx Agent Boilerplate — a Next.js app (also compatible with React and Vue) that uses the internal Strand design system.

## Critical: Read the SSOT First

Before generating ANY UI code, you MUST read and follow:

  docs/STRANDS_AGENT_RULES.md

This file is the Single Source of Truth (SSOT) for all design tokens, color values, typography, spacing, button variants, icons, and mandatory rules.

## Quick Reference

- **Colors:** Use Strand semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-text-primary`, `bg-accent`) — never hardcode hex values.
- **Typography:** Noto Sans (body), IBM Plex Mono (code), Milling Duplex (brand). NOT Inter.
- **Spacing:** 4px grid. Use `p-1` through `p-16` (maps to 4px–64px).
- **Buttons:** 6 sizes (mini → xlarge) × 11 variants. Hover: radius bumps up one token step.
- **Border Radius:** `rounded-sm` (4px) through `rounded-full` (pill).
- **Dark Mode:** `class="dark"` on `<html>` — all semantic colors auto-swap.
- **Icons:** 16×16 SVG from `strand/icons/`, use `currentColor`.
- **Content Max:** 1200px. Chat Max: 800px. Header: 56px.

## Token Files

- `strand/tokens/colors.json` — complete color palette
- `strand/tokens/typography.json` — font families and size scale
- `strand/tokens/spacing.json` — spacing, sizing, layout
- `strand/tokens/buttons.json` — button sizes, variants, hover
- `strand/tokens/radii.json` — border radius
- `strand/tokens/shadows.json` — box shadows
- `strand/tokens/icons.json` — icon manifest
- `strand/css/variables.css` — all tokens as CSS custom properties
- `strand/tailwind-preset.js` — Tailwind v3 preset (React/Vue)

## Framework Support

- **Next.js:** Tokens already in `globals.css` via `@theme inline` (Tailwind v4)
- **React (Vite):** Use `strand/tailwind-preset.js` as preset + import `strand/css/variables.css`
- **Vue:** Same Tailwind preset or use raw `var(--strand-*)` CSS properties

## Rules

1. Never hardcode hex colors — use Strand Tailwind classes or CSS vars
2. Never use Inter as primary font — Noto Sans is the fallback
3. All spacing must be on the 4px grid
4. Use only the defined button variants from buttons.json
5. Dark mode uses class strategy, not prefers-color-scheme
6. Icons are 16×16 SVG with currentColor stroke
7. No emoji in UI — never use emoji in buttons, labels, headings, or body text
8. White-majority aesthetic — default background is pure white (#FFFFFF), use #F4F3F3 sparingly for card accents
9. No login screens — sample apps use API keys via env vars or inline input, not auth flows
10. Professional, purposeful design — every component must demonstrate real TwelveLabs API impact
11. Minimalistic layout — generous whitespace, thin borders (#E8E7E5), charcoal pill buttons with arrow icons
12. Study twelvelabs.io for correct aesthetic — white backgrounds, bold sans-serif type, restrained color
